data.value: A longitude value is needed for sidereal time calculations. To find your longitude, use the Google map below. Find and then right click on your location. Your longitude will be the second number, on the upper right as shown in the example. Note, if you live in the western hemisphere, be sure to include a minus sign before your longitude as shown. Your longitude is stored only in the local OPL database on your machine. If you would prefer to not provide your longitude, leave the value blank and it will be set to the Prime Meridian Line of 0 degrees. In that instance, be aware that the sidereal time calculations will not be accurate for your location. To edit your longitude later, go to Tools -> Settings. (If you don't see the Google map below please install Microsoft's WebView2 control available from https://developer.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoft-edge/webview2/)
